# üèõÔ∏è AI Museum Curator ‚Äî Greek Mythology Edition

Interactive Streamlit web app that combines MET Museum data with OpenAI to create curator-quality artwork interpretations and a rich interactive zone.

---

## üéÆ Quick Start ‚Äî How to Use

1. Open the **Greek Deities** tab.  
2. Select a figure from the dropdown. Read the short fixed bio. Click **"Expand description with AI"** to get a museum-style introduction.  
3. Click **"Fetch related works from MET"** to gather candidate artworks.  
4. Go to **Works & Analysis**, choose a thumbnail, then click **"Generate AI Curatorial Analysis"**.  
5. Explore **Interactive Art Zone** for hands-on tools:
   - Detail & Symbolism (ask about visual elements)
   - Style Analyzer (upload a sketch/photo for style matching)
   - Myth Identifier (describe a scene to identify the deity)
   - Which God Are You? (short personality quiz)
   - Myth Image Generator (AI image from text prompt)

---

## ‚úÖ Key Features

- Dropdown selection of Greek figures with fixed bios + AI expansion.  
- Automatic MET searches using aliases for broader recall.  
- Thumbnail gallery and high-resolution artwork viewer.  
- AI-generated curator analyses with structured sections.  
- Interactive Art Zone with multiple user-facing tools (detail analysis, style-matching, myth ID, personality quiz, DALL¬∑E image generation).

---

## üß† Technical Stack

- Streamlit (UI)  
- OpenAI (Chat + Image APIs)  
- MET Museum Open API (art data)  
- Python (requests, Pillow, dotenv)

